1
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:09,433
<i>Why can't we take him
to the hospital?</i>

2
00:00:09,433 --> 00:00:10,400
<i> We can't!</i>

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,100
<i>If this gets reported
to the police,</i>

4
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:13,633
<i>they'll find out Jalil
is still alive!</i>

5
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,533
We need to be careful here too.

6
00:00:15,667 --> 00:00:16,700
<i> There are too many civilians.</i>

7
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,533
<i>We can't let them
get dragged into this again.</i>

8
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:21,367
<i>Agent Angeles, this is the
composite sketch I made.</i>

9
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:22,767
<i> Take a look. Is it accurate?</i>

10
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:28,333
<i>The suspect is an
unidentified male.</i>

11
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:29,900
<i> Study the facial composite.</i>

12
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,233
<i> Memorize the face.</i>

13
00:00:31,767 --> 00:00:34,400
<i>Sir Omar, there are people
outside! The police!</i>

14
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:37,067
<i> The police will see Jalil!</i>

15
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:38,767
<i> I won't allow that!</i>

16
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:40,233
<i> I know a doctor.</i>

17
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:42,433
<i>She's kind, but she strictly
follows the law.</i>

18
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:44,133
<i> We don't mean any harm.</i>

19
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:45,967
<i>We're just here
to ask questions.</i>

20
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:47,400
<i> Why did you bring them here?</i>

21
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,300
<i>- We're looking for someone.
- You're Muslim too.</i>

22
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:51,567
<i>You know it's forbidden for us
to harbor criminals.</i>

23
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:52,467
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

24
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:54,300
<i> Look, we're being raided</i>

25
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:56,267
<i>even though we haven't
done anything wrong!</i>

26
00:00:56,367 --> 00:00:57,933
<i> What's Reyes doing there?</i>

27
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,267
<i>He's here to identify
the target.</i>

28
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:04,467
<i>Just make sure you catch
whoever you're after!</i>

29
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:05,933
<i> Who can we talk to here?</i>

30
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,267
Do you have a barangay captain?

31
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,100
<i>Yes, Omar.
His house is over there.</i>

32
00:01:10,167 --> 00:01:11,233
<i> Who--oh!</i>

33
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:13,500
<i>- Is Omar here?
- What do you need him for?</i>

34
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:15,133
<i> Do you know this criminal?</i>

35
00:01:15,133 --> 00:01:16,300
<i> Look closely.</i>

36
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:18,533
<i> There's no criminal here.</i>

37
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:19,833
<i> Sorry.</i>

38
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:23,333
<i>Command, negative on visuals.
No signs of the suspect.</i>

39
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,467
<i> Doctor, I need your help.</i>

40
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:26,833
<i> I'm almost at your house.</i>

41
00:01:27,167 --> 00:01:27,933
<i> Doc!</i>

42
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:44,133
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:01:53,667 --> 00:02:00,567
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:02:14,767 --> 00:02:21,700
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

45
00:02:22,767 --> 00:02:23,833
Forcep.

46
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,867
[GROANING]

47
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:36,533
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

48
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:38,333
[SIGHS IN RELIEF]

49
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,200
Silk suture.

50
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:42,200
[PHONE VIBRATING]

51
00:02:43,533 --> 00:02:45,733
[LINE RINGING]

52
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:52,700
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

53
00:02:58,433 --> 00:03:00,100
Thank you so much, Doc.

54
00:03:00,433 --> 00:03:01,733
Sorry for the trouble.

55
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,433
And thank you for lending us
your son's T-shirt.

56
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,467
[CHUCKLES]

57
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:08,933
Come on, Omar.
This is no trouble at all.

58
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:11,967
It's good that he's stable now.

59
00:03:12,133 --> 00:03:13,067
Is it Jalil?

60
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,567
Yes, Jalil.

61
00:03:15,233 --> 00:03:18,267
Uh, I've already given him
antibiotics.

62
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,733
But I'll give you
a prescription

63
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:21,267
so you can continue it.

64
00:03:22,467 --> 00:03:24,567
Now, for the police report,

65
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,300
what's Jalil's full name?

66
00:03:26,467 --> 00:03:30,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:32,833
Uh, Doc...

68
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:36,433
I know it's your duty to
report this to the police.

69
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:40,367
But I just want to say...

70
00:03:40,367 --> 00:03:41,967
...you know me.

71
00:03:41,967 --> 00:03:43,767
I don't harbor criminals.

72
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:46,633
Jalil isn't a bad person.

73
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:56,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

74
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:02,633
Thank you.

75
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:05,767
Thank you...

76
00:04:06,233 --> 00:04:07,400
...so much.

77
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:11,967
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

78
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:13,633
I'll leave you for now, okay?

79
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,500
Thank you, Doc.

80
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:24,333
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

81
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:27,367
- [BOTH GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

82
00:04:28,867 --> 00:04:30,833
[GRUNTING]

83
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:34,500
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

84
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:39,967
[GLASS SHATTERING]

85
00:04:44,533 --> 00:04:45,667
You bastard.

86
00:04:47,267 --> 00:04:48,700
You'll get what's coming
to you.

87
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:52,033
Jalil, how are you feeling?

88
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:56,067
We're lucky the doctor
let us come here.

89
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:59,700
Yeah. She's really kind.

90
00:05:01,367 --> 00:05:02,567
[OMAR] It's just sad that

91
00:05:02,967 --> 00:05:05,000
one of her children
died early.

92
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:06,767
What?

93
00:05:10,367 --> 00:05:11,400
[MAN] Hey!

94
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,433
[GROANING] Come here!

95
00:05:15,633 --> 00:05:18,200
Go buy me more alcohol
from the store.

96
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,367
Tell them I'll pay tomorrow.

97
00:05:20,367 --> 00:05:22,033
But Pa, you're already drunk.

98
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:23,000
So what?!

99
00:05:23,133 --> 00:05:25,767
You talk too much!
Just go buy it!

100
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:29,333
Pa, please stop! Have mercy!

101
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,867
[BLOW LANDS]

102
00:05:31,567 --> 00:05:33,467
Are you crazy?!

103
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:35,767
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- He's just a kid...

104
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,567
...and you're hitting him?!

105
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:39,967
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [YELLS]

106
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:48,800
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:05:50,067 --> 00:05:51,533
Don't! Don't be scared.

108
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:54,733
I'm on your side.

109
00:05:57,467 --> 00:05:58,633
Are you okay?

110
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:01,033
- Huh?
- [CRYING]

111
00:06:02,467 --> 00:06:03,933
Stay strong, alright?

112
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:09,500
Okay.

113
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:15,800
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

114
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:22,767
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

115
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:47,933
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:07:00,633 --> 00:07:01,667
Uncle!

117
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:09,700
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,033
That's the doctor's son?

119
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:13,767
Yeah.

120
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,433
He's the one who caught Father.

121
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:17,733
He's also the one
looking for Jalil now!

122
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:19,367
- What?
- Yes.

123
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:24,067
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

124
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,067
We need to leave.

125
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:28,467
[PHONE RINGING]

126
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:30,867
[RINGING CONTINUES]

127
00:07:31,567 --> 00:07:33,767
[LINE RINGING]

128
00:07:33,767 --> 00:07:40,700
[RINGING CONTINUES]

129
00:07:41,567 --> 00:07:42,933
Marcus, son.

130
00:07:42,933 --> 00:07:44,567
Ma, why did you only
answer now?

131
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:46,967
I'm on my way home.

132
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:48,533
You're on your way home?

133
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:50,600
Yes, Ma.

134
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,867
I'm already at the
subdivision gate.

135
00:07:53,633 --> 00:07:58,400
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

136
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:07,100
Alright, son. Be careful.

137
00:08:09,033 --> 00:08:13,000
Omar, my son from SID
is on his way home.

138
00:08:13,433 --> 00:08:14,967
- We're leaving now, Doc.
- Let's go.

139
00:08:14,967 --> 00:08:17,000
- Come on.
- Jalil, let's go.

140
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,533
Uh, Doc.

141
00:08:21,933 --> 00:08:24,133
I'm not asking you to keep
secrets from your son,

142
00:08:24,133 --> 00:08:27,700
but I'll say it again,
I don't harbor criminals.

143
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,900
- Jalil is a good person.
- Yes.

144
00:08:32,933 --> 00:08:34,967
Take it slow, okay?
Your wound might reopen.

145
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:43,900
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

146
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:45,600
Thank you.

147
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:49,567
Thank you.

148
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:51,933
[JAMILAH] Jalil, we need to go.

149
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:53,933
- Let's go, Jalil.
- [GROANS]

150
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,633
- Careful, his wounds.
- Thank you so much!

151
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:58,300
- Thank you, Doc!
- Take care.

152
00:08:58,467 --> 00:08:59,600
Get well soon.

153
00:08:59,933 --> 00:09:04,667
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

154
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:06,433
[JAMILAH] Hurry!

155
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:08,467
Hurry, he might get here!

156
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:13,100
[JALIL GROANING]

157
00:09:13,967 --> 00:09:20,067
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:09:20,467 --> 00:09:21,333
Hurry!

159
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:22,633
Hurry, Jalil!

160
00:09:23,133 --> 00:09:25,300
- [OMAR] Go!
- He might catch up to us!

161
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:32,233
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

162
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:37,967
[JALIL GROANING]

163
00:09:39,667 --> 00:09:46,600
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

164
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:06,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:10:25,367 --> 00:10:26,867
Son, what happened to you?

166
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:30,200
It's nothing, Mom.

167
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,733
Oh, uh...

168
00:10:35,367 --> 00:10:36,733
Let me do that, Mom.

169
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:38,233
No, I've got it.

170
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:40,933
Just eat first.

171
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:43,033
I'll take care of it.

172
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:48,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

173
00:10:54,067 --> 00:10:58,233
[MUSIC TURNS UNSETTLING]

174
00:10:58,367 --> 00:10:59,267
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

175
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,933
[TERESA]
<i> What's your name?</i>

176
00:11:01,367 --> 00:11:02,600
<i> Can you hear me?</i>

177
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:04,867
[WEAKLY] Jalil.

178
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,667
Who is this, son?

179
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,233
[GLASS CLINKS]

180
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:19,133
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:11:19,467 --> 00:11:21,367
I had an encounter
with him earlier.

182
00:11:22,733 --> 00:11:23,967
He's the suspect we chased.

183
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,233
What did he do?

184
00:11:30,233 --> 00:11:32,100
He and Datu Rahman
are from the same village.

185
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:35,967
And I found him earlier
at the same place

186
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:38,367
where Datu Rahman was brought.

187
00:11:38,733 --> 00:11:43,033
I think he holds the answers
to my questions.

188
00:11:43,167 --> 00:11:47,600
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

189
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,167
Are you alright, Ma?

190
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:50,400
Um...

191
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:52,467
I'm just tired, son.

192
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:53,900
Um...

193
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:55,967
I'll go throw away the garbage.

194
00:11:56,167 --> 00:11:57,267
Wait, do you want to eat?

195
00:11:57,367 --> 00:11:58,467
I'm good.

196
00:11:58,667 --> 00:12:00,267
I'm going to sleep already.

197
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,800
- Good night.
- Good night.

198
00:12:05,033 --> 00:12:12,000
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

199
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,867
[AZUELO]
Reyes is out of control!

200
00:12:18,967 --> 00:12:21,800
And you're backing him!

201
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,500
Sir, do you know
how I found the warehouse?

202
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,667
By following Agent Reyes.

203
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,500
So you admit he's investigating
despite being suspended?

204
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:35,100
Is he trying to get himself
removed from service?

205
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:37,133
Sir, that's not my point.

206
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:40,767
My point is, suspending him
was the wrong move.

207
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:41,933
And how is that possible?

208
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:45,967
He seriously screwed up
your last mission!

209
00:12:46,067 --> 00:12:49,000
And now he's disrespecting
me and the agency

210
00:12:49,033 --> 00:12:52,300
by taking that suspension
for granted!

211
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:55,333
It'll be easier
to solve the case

212
00:12:55,533 --> 00:12:57,733
if you let Agent Reyes return.

213
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,033
No!

214
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:01,033
He needs to learn.

215
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:03,900
Even you,
Agent Angeles.

216
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:07,533
Well, maybe this
will convince you.

217
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:12,200
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

218
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,933
"Most incompetent SID Director
in Philippine History"

219
00:13:13,933 --> 00:13:15,767
"Hahaha"

220
00:13:15,767 --> 00:13:17,200
"Lazy"

221
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,367
"Useless"

222
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:22,333
Did you see the comments, sir?

223
00:13:22,733 --> 00:13:24,533
Everyone is criticizing you.

224
00:13:26,033 --> 00:13:28,867
The only way to solve this case
once and for all,

225
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:30,500
is to bring back
your top agent.

226
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:38,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

227
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:51,833
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:11,567
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:14:26,433 --> 00:14:28,233
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

230
00:14:28,433 --> 00:14:30,267
- [GUNSHOT]
<i> -</i> [MARCUS] Felix!

231
00:14:31,967 --> 00:14:33,567
- [MARCUS]<i> Enough!
</i>- [LARA] Stand down!

232
00:14:33,767 --> 00:14:35,433
<i> That animal is wanted!</i>

233
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:37,433
<i> -</i> [LARA]<i> Stand down!
</i>- [MARCUS]<i> We need him alive.</i>

234
00:14:40,533 --> 00:14:42,133
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

235
00:14:42,133 --> 00:14:43,100
<i> Father!</i>

236
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:45,433
<i>- This is an ambush!
- Hold your fire!</i>

237
00:14:45,633 --> 00:14:52,433
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

238
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:14,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:15:23,533 --> 00:15:24,633
Cuchy.

240
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,167
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

241
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:33,367
Mm...

242
00:15:35,067 --> 00:15:37,167
Come here, sweetie.

243
00:15:38,667 --> 00:15:39,700
How are you?

244
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,700
Don't be sad, okay?

245
00:15:48,367 --> 00:15:49,400
Don't worry.

246
00:15:51,167 --> 00:15:53,067
I'll take good care of you.

247
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:58,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

248
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:00,367
[MARCUS]
<i> Are you an ally...</i>

249
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:03,033
<i>or an accomplice
in all of this?</i>

250
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:10,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:16:15,233 --> 00:16:18,700
- Lay him down, Omar.
- Slowly, Jalil.

252
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:20,200
- [JALIL GRUNTS]
- There.

253
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,167
Alright.

254
00:16:21,433 --> 00:16:22,400
Oh, Omar,

255
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:26,533
what a kind person
that doctor you know is.

256
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:30,733
[JAMILAH]
We almost got caught, Auntie.

257
00:16:31,133 --> 00:16:34,033
The doctor is
Marcus Reyes's mother.

258
00:16:34,367 --> 00:16:36,767
But she protected us
from her son.

259
00:16:37,433 --> 00:16:41,167
Now, is your brother is safe.

260
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:44,700
Thank you.

261
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:51,567
You risked your lives
to save me.

262
00:16:51,733 --> 00:16:55,067
Jalil, you are one of us.

263
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,367
We are family.

264
00:16:57,600 --> 00:17:00,567
We will always protect
you and Jamilah.

265
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,300
Are you okay?

266
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:11,067
Thank you.

267
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:17,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

268
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:29,167
[THUNDER CLAPS]

269
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,600
<i> Gabriel, don't let go!</i>

270
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:35,800
<i>- Hold on!
- Marcus!</i>

271
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,600
<i>- Help me!
- Hold on!</i>

272
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:41,433
<i>- Marcus!
- Aah!</i>

273
00:17:41,433 --> 00:17:42,433
<i>- Gabriel!
- [WAVE CRASHES]</i>

274
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:44,300
Gabriel!

275
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:47,600
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

276
00:17:49,167 --> 00:17:56,133
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

277
00:18:01,533 --> 00:18:03,167
[TV REPORTER]
<i> Police are now searching</i>

278
00:18:03,167 --> 00:18:05,333
<i> for an unidentified male</i>

279
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:10,167
<i>following an encounter
with NLEA and SID operatives</i>

280
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,800
<i>at a warehouse believed
to have been a hideout</i>

281
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:15,467
<i>and now fugitive
of gun  muggler</i>

282
00:18:15,633 --> 00:18:17,033
<i> Datu</i> Rahman Abubakar.

283
00:18:17,133 --> 00:18:19,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,833
[TV REPORTER]
<i> Authorities believe that</i>

285
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,467
<i>Datu Rahman Abubakar
managed to escape,</i>

286
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:26,333
<i>leaving the man behind
to confront members</i>

287
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:28,833
<i>of Task Force Alpha
during last night's operation.</i>

288
00:18:29,167 --> 00:18:32,967
<i>If you know this man
or where he is,</i>

289
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:37,233
<i>please contact the numbers
on your screen.</i>

290
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:38,467
[WOMAN] Actually,

291
00:18:38,733 --> 00:18:41,033
<i>my client, who wants
to remain anonymous,</i>

292
00:18:41,033 --> 00:18:42,800
<i>has donated a reward
of two million pesos</i>

293
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:45,567
<i>for anyone who can
provide information</i>

294
00:18:45,867 --> 00:18:49,067
<i>about the whereabouts
not only of Datu Rahman,</i>

295
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:51,633
<i>but also of this
unidentified suspect.</i>

296
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:54,233
[FIELD REPORTER]<i> Why is your
</i> client doing this, Attorney?

297
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,533
[ATTORNEY]
<i> Let's just say</i>

298
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:58,233
<i>my client's family
was a victim of gun violence.</i>

299
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,600
<i> And it's their advocacy now</i>

300
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:00,700
<i>to prevent this from
happening to others.</i>

301
00:19:00,767 --> 00:19:07,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

302
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:15,067
[GRUNTS WEAKLY]

303
00:19:16,733 --> 00:19:19,700
[OMAR]<i> Doc,
</i> I know you're obligated

304
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,267
<i> to report this to the police,</i>

305
00:19:21,367 --> 00:19:25,700
<i> but... you know me.</i>

306
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:28,100
<i> I would never help a criminal.</i>

307
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,900
<i> Jalil is not a bad person.</i>

308
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:32,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

309
00:19:32,967 --> 00:19:33,933
[TERESA]
<i> Who is this, son?</i>

310
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:35,533
<i>I had an encounter
with him earlier.</i>

311
00:19:35,767 --> 00:19:37,067
<i> He's the suspect we chased.</i>

312
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:44,233
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

313
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:11,667
<i>They're still holding
Datu Rahman captive</i>

314
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,467
<i>because they need
something from him.</i>

315
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:14,567
<i> But who are they?</i>

316
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:17,000
<i>And what do they
need from Datu Rahman?</i>

317
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:19,400
<i> Everyone is criticizing you.</i>

318
00:20:19,633 --> 00:20:22,333
The only way to solve this case
<i> once and for all,</i>

319
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:24,167
<i>is to bring back
your top agent.</i>

320
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:27,000
<i>Make sure I'll be able
to talk to him</i>

321
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,267
<i> before his cabinet meeting.</i>

322
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:29,400
<i> Yes, sir.</i>

323
00:20:31,033 --> 00:20:33,267
<i>You're taking this mission
too personally,</i>

324
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:34,767
<i>so I'm keeping
a close eye on you.</i>

325
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:37,000
<i>I need to know
your every move.</i>

326
00:20:37,167 --> 00:20:37,800
<i> Understood?</i>

327
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:38,800
<i> Yes, ma'am.</i>

328
00:20:39,033 --> 00:20:41,967
<i>If you know this man
or where he is,</i>

329
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:43,167
<i>please contact the numbers
on your screen.</i>

330
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:44,500
<i> That's Jalil!</i>

331
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:46,500
<i> There's a huge reward for him.</i>

332
00:20:46,667 --> 00:20:48,767
<i>A criminal has infiltrated
our community.</i>

333
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:52,100
<i>Did I make the
right decision?</i>

334
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:55,467
<i>Am I really helping
a good person?</i>

335
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:57,300
<i> Or is he a criminal?</i>

336
00:20:58,333 --> 00:21:01,167
<i>You're wanted, and there's
a bounty on your head.</i>

337
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:05,300
Please, leave them out of this.
<i> Just take me.</i>

338
00:21:05,567 --> 00:21:09,133
<i>I finally found a tenant
for this unit!</i>

339
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,133
<i>Could you give me a tour
of the place?</i>

340
00:21:11,233 --> 00:21:14,700
<i>I'd like to meet
my new neighbors.</i>

341
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:16,167
<i>I'll introduce you
to them!</i>
